items.title: China's Latest Bid to Boost Stocks Barely Moves the Needle
items.description: Authorities’ request for state-owned insurance companies and mutual funds to invest more in stocks got a lackluster market reaction.

items.title: S&P 500, Nasdaq Futures Slip
items.description: Stock futures dipped as investors juggled the implications of Trump 2.0 with AI excitement and earnings.

items.title: Higher Yields Aren't a Scare, Bodes Well for Bigger Bond Returns
items.description: The 10-year Treasury yield was rising and AXA Investment Managers said the world isn’t walking away from bonds despite higher yields.

items.title: Bank of Japan Must Weigh Trump Trade Threats as it Tightens Policy
items.description: Setting rates in Japan will become a delicate balancing act if tariffs materialize.

items.title: Are the L.A. Wildfires One Catastrophe or Two? It Matters to Insurers
items.description: Some insurers may be able to collect more on their own insurance if they treat the Palisades and Eaton fires as separate events.
